<section xml:id="C14.S17">
<title>Integrals</title>         
<subsection xml:id="C14.S17.SS1">
<title>Indefinite Integrals</title>          
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="14.17.1" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E1">{\int\left(1-x^{2}\right)^{-\mu/2}\mathsf{P}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathrm{ d}x}={-\left(1-x^{2}\right)^{-(\mu-1)/2}\mathsf{P}^{\mu-1}_{\nu}\left(x\right)}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="14.17.2" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E2">\int\left(1-x^{2}\right)^{\mu/2}\mathsf{P}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathrm{d} x=\frac{\left(1-x^{2}\right)^{(\mu+1)/2}}{(\nu-\mu)(\nu+\mu+1)}\mathsf{P}^{\mu +1}_{\nu}\left(x\right), if \mu\neq\nu or -\nu-1</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
  
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p2.s1">
 <Math equation-number="14.17.3" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E3">\int x\mathsf{P}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right) \mathrm{d}x=\frac{1}{2\nu(\nu+1)}\left((\mu^{2}-(\nu+1)(\nu+x^{2}))\mathsf{P}^ {\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right)+(\nu+1)(\nu-\mu+ 1)x(\mathsf{P}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}^{\mu}_{\nu+1}\left(x\right) +\mathsf{P}^{\mu}_{\nu+1}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right))-( \nu-\mu+1)^{2}\mathsf{P}^{\mu}_{\nu+1}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}^{\mu}_{\nu+1} \left(x\right)\right), if \nu\neq 0,-1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p2.s2">
<Math equation-number="14.17.4" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E4">\int\frac{x}{\left(1-x^{2}\right)^{3/2}}\mathsf{P}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right) \mathsf{Q}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathrm{d}x=\frac{1}{\left(1-4\mu^{2} \right)\left(1-x^{2}\right)^{1/2}}\left((1-2\mu^{2}+2\nu(\nu+1))\mathsf{P}^{ \mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right)+(2\nu+1)(\mu-\nu- 1)x(\mathsf{P}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}^{\mu}_{\nu+1}\left(x\right) +\mathsf{P}^{\mu}_{\nu+1}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}^{\mu}_{\nu}\left(x\right))+2 (\mu-\nu-1)^{2}\mathsf{P}^{\mu}_{\nu+1}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}^{\mu}_{\nu+1} \left(x\right)\right), if \mu\neq\pm\frac{1}{2}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p2.s3">
In (14.17.1)–(14.17.4),
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p2.s4">
<Math mode="inline" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p2.m1">\mathsf{P}</Math> may be replaced by <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p2.m2">\mathsf{Q}</Math> , and in (14.17.3) and (14.17.4),
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p2.s5">
<Math mode="inline" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p2.m3">\mathsf{Q}</Math> may be replaced by <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p2.m4">\mathsf{P}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p3.s1">
For further results, see Maximon (1955) andPrudnikov et al. (1990, pp. 37–39).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C14.S17.SS1.p3.s2">
See also (14.12.2), (14.12.5), and (14.12.12).
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C14.S17.SS2">
<title>Barnes’ Integral</title>            
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C14.S17.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="14.17.5" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E5">\int_{0}^{1}x^{\sigma}\left(1-x^{2}\right)^{\mu/2}\mathsf{P}^{-\mu}_{\nu}\left (x\right)\mathrm{d}x=\frac{\Gamma\left(\frac{1}{2}\sigma+\frac{1}{2}\right) \Gamma\left(\frac{1}{2}\sigma+1\right)}{2^{\mu+1}\Gamma\left(\frac{1}{2}\sigma -\frac{1}{2}\nu+\frac{1}{2}\mu+1\right)\Gamma\left(\frac{1}{2}\sigma+\frac{1}{ 2}\nu+\frac{1}{2}\mu+\frac{3}{2}\right)}, if \Re\sigma&gt;-1, \Re\mu&gt;-1</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C14.S17.SS3">
<title>Orthogonality Properties</title>        
      
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C14.S17.SS3.p1.s1">
For <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C14.S17.SS3.p1.m1">l,m,n=0,1,2,\dots</Math> , <Math equation-number="14.17.6" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E6">\int_{-1}^{1}\mathsf{P}^{m}_{l}\left(x\right)\mathsf{P}^{m}_{n}\left(x\right) \mathrm{d}x=\frac{(n+m)!}{(n-m)!\left(n+\frac{1}{2}\right)}\delta_{l,n}</Math> , <Math equation-number="14.17.7" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E7">\int_{-1}^{1}\mathsf{P}^{m}_{l}\left(x\right)\mathsf{P}^{-m}_{n}\left(x\right) \mathrm{d}x=\frac{(-1)^{m}}{l+\frac{1}{2}}\delta_{l,n},</Math> , <Math equation-number="14.17.8" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E8">\int_{-1}^{1}\frac{\mathsf{P}^{l}_{n}\left(x\right)\mathsf{P}^{m}_{n}\left(x \right)}{1-x^{2}}\mathrm{d}x=\frac{(n+m)!}{(n-m)!m}\delta_{l,m}, if m&gt;0,</Math> , <Math equation-number="14.17.9" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E9">\int_{-1}^{1}\frac{\mathsf{P}^{l}_{n}\left(x\right)\mathsf{P}^{-m}_{n}\left(x \right)}{1-x^{2}}\mathrm{d}x=\frac{(-1)^{l}}{l}\delta_{l,m}, if l&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS3.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="12" xml:id="C14.S17.SS3.p2.s1">
Orthogonality relations for the associated Legendre functions of imaginary order are given in Bielski (2013).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C14.S17.SS4">
<title>Definite Integrals of Products</title>           
 
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="13" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p1.s1">
With <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p1.m1">\psi\left(x\right)=\Gamma'\left(x\right)/\Gamma\left(x\right)</Math> (§5.2(i)),
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="14" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="14.17.10" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E10">\int_{-1}^{1}\mathsf{P}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathsf{P}_{\lambda}\left(x\right) \mathrm{d}x=\frac{2\left(2\sin\left(\nu\pi\right)\sin\left(\lambda\pi\right) \left(\psi\left(\nu+1\right)-\psi\left(\lambda+1\right)\right)+\pi\sin\left(( \lambda-\nu)\pi\right)\right)}{\pi^{2}(\lambda-\nu)(\lambda+\nu+1)}, if \lambda\neq\nu or -\nu-1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="15" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="14.17.11" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E11">\int_{-1}^{1}\left(\mathsf{P}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\right)^{2}\mathrm{d}x=\frac{ \pi^{2}-2{\sin^{2}}\left(\nu\pi\right)\psi'\left(\nu+1\right)}{\pi^{2}\left( \nu+\frac{1}{2}\right)}, if \nu\neq-\frac{1}{2}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="16" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="14.17.12" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E12">\int_{-1}^{1}\mathsf{Q}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}_{\lambda}\left(x\right) \mathrm{d}x=\frac{\left((\psi\left(\nu+1\right)-\psi\left(\lambda+1\right))(1+ \cos\left(\nu\pi\right)\cos\left(\lambda\pi\right))+\frac{1}{2}\pi\sin\left(( \lambda-\nu)\pi\right)\right)}{(\lambda-\nu)(\lambda+\nu+1)}, if \lambda\neq\nu or -\nu-1, \lambda\text{ and }\nu\neq-1,-2,-3,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="17" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p1.s5">
<Math equation-number="14.17.13" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E13">\int_{-1}^{1}\left(\mathsf{Q}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\right)^{2}\mathrm{d}x=\frac{ \pi^{2}-2\left(1+{\cos^{2}}\left(\nu\pi\right)\right)\psi'\left(\nu+1\right)}{ 2(2\nu+1)}, if \nu\neq-\frac{1}{2} or -1,-2,-3,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="6" sentence-num-in-section="18" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p1.s6">
<Math equation-number="14.17.14" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E14">\int_{-1}^{1}\mathsf{P}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}_{\lambda}\left(x\right) \mathrm{d}x=\frac{2\sin\left(\nu\pi\right)\cos\left(\lambda\pi\right)\left( \psi\left(\nu+1\right)-\psi\left(\lambda+1\right)\right)+\pi\cos\left((\lambda -\nu)\pi\right)-\pi}{\pi(\lambda-\nu)(\lambda+\nu+1)}, if \Re\lambda&gt;0, \Re\nu&gt;0, \lambda\neq\nu</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
  
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="19" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p2.s1">
 <Math equation-number="14.17.15" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E15">\int_{-1}^{1}\mathsf{P}_{\nu}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}_{\nu}\left(x\right) \mathrm{d}x=-\frac{\sin\left(2\nu\pi\right)\psi'\left(\nu+1\right)}{\pi(2\nu+1 )}, if \Re\nu&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="20" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p2.s2">
<Math equation-number="14.17.16" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E16">\int_{-1}^{1}\mathsf{P}^{m}_{l}\left(x\right)\mathsf{Q}^{m}_{n}\left(x\right) \mathrm{d}x=\frac{\left(1-(-1)^{l+n}\right)(l+m)!}{(l-n)(l+n+1)(l-m)!}, if l,m,n=0,1,2,\dots, l\neq n</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="21" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p2.s3">
<Math equation-number="14.17.17" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E17">\int_{0}^{\pi}\mathsf{Q}_{l}\left(\cos\theta\right)\mathsf{P}_{m}\left(\cos \theta\right)\mathsf{P}_{n}\left(\cos\theta\right)\sin\theta\mathrm{d}\theta=0, if l,m,n=1,2,3,\dots, |m-n|&lt;l&lt;m+n</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="22" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p2.s4">
(When <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p2.m1">l+m+n</Math> is even the condition <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p2.m2">\left|m-n\right|&lt;l&lt;m+n</Math> is not needed.)Next,
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="23" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p2.s5">
<Math equation-number="14.17.18" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E18">\int_{1}^{\infty}P_{\nu}\left(x\right)Q_{\lambda}\left(x\right)\mathrm{d}x= \frac{1}{(\lambda-\nu)(\nu+\lambda+1)}, if \Re\lambda&gt;\Re\nu&gt;0.</Math>
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="6" sentence-num-in-section="24" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p2.s6">
 <Math equation-number="14.17.19" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E19">\int_{1}^{\infty}Q_{\nu}\left(x\right)Q_{\lambda}\left(x\right)\mathrm{d}x= \frac{\psi\left(\lambda+1\right)-\psi\left(\nu+1\right)}{(\lambda-\nu)(\lambda +\nu+1)}, if \Re(\lambda+\nu)&gt;-1, \lambda\neq\nu, \lambda and \nu\neq-1,-2,-3,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="7" sentence-num-in-section="25" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p2.s7">
<Math equation-number="14.17.20" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S17.E20">\int_{1}^{\infty}(Q_{\nu}\left(x\right))^{2}\mathrm{d}x=\frac{\psi'\left(\nu+1 \right)}{2\nu+1}, if \Re\nu&gt;-\tfrac{1}{2}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="26" xml:id="C14.S17.SS4.p3.s1">
For further results, see Prudnikov et al. (1990, pp. 194–240); also (34.3.21).
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C14.S17.SS5">
<title>Laplace Transforms</title>          
 
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS5.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="27" xml:id="C14.S17.SS5.p1.s1">
For Laplace transforms and inverse Laplace transforms involving associated Legendre functions, seeErdélyi et al. (1954a, pp. 179–181, 270–272),Oberhettinger and Badii (1973, pp. 113–118, 317–324),Prudnikov et al. (1992a, §§3.22,3.32, and 3.33), andPrudnikov et al. (1992b, §§3.20, 3.30, and 3.31).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C14.S17.SS6">
<title>Mellin Transforms</title>          
 
<para xml:id="C14.S17.SS6.p1">

